{"id":"328008110_Finding_tendencies_in_streaming_data_using_Big_Data_frequent_itemset_mining","abstract":"The amount of information generated in social media channels or economical/business transactions exceeds the usual bounds of static databases and is in continuous growing. In this work, we propose a frequent itemset mining method using sliding windows capable of extracting tendencies from continuous data flows. For that aim, we develop this method using Big Data technologies, in particular, using the Spark Streaming framework enabling distributing the computation along several clusters and thus improving the algorithm speed. The experimentation carried out shows the capability of our proposal and its scalability when massive amounts of data coming from streams are taken into account.","authors":["Carlos Fernandez-Basso","Abel J. Francisco-Agra","Maria J. Martin-Bautista","M. Dolores Ruiz"],"meta":["October 2018Knowledge-Based Systems 163","DOI:10.1016/j.knosys.2018.09.026","Project: Fuzzy association rules in Big Data"],"references":["303912344_R-Apriori_An_Efficient_Apriori_based_Algorithm_on_Spark","282909044_Performance_Analysis_of_Apriori_Algorithm_with_Different_Data_Structures_on_Hadoop_Cluster","272864559_Comparing_the_Performance_of_Frequent_Pattern_Mining_Algorithms","262233351_Resilient_distributed_datasets_A_fault-tolerant_abstraction_for_in-memory_cluster_computing","221654028_New_Algorithms_for_Fast_Discovery_of_Association_Rules","220895561_Approximately_Mining_Recently_Representative_Patterns_on_Data_Streams","220894927_GC-Tree_A_Fast_Online_Algorithm_for_Mining_Frequent_Closed_Itemsets","220520017_Algorithms_for_Association_Rule_Mining_-_A_General_Survey_and_Comparison","312775005_MapReduce_Simplified_data_processing_on_large_clusters","299476405_High_Utility_Pattern_Mining_over_Data_Streams_with_Sliding_Window_Technique","289694667_Sliding_window_based_weighted_erasable_stream_pattern_mining_for_stream_data_applications","262216399_Accelerating_